## Notes

- Fill in `experiment.yaml` before submitting any real jobs.
- Replace the generated scaffold scripts (`train.py`, `eval.py`, `train_adapter.py`) with
  your actual training code, or point `model.script` at an existing entrypoint.
- `model.script` must be a training entrypoint script (not a module that only defines classes).
- If eval is enabled, `eval.train_outputs` controls whether eval consumes the
  `latest`, `best`, or an `explicit` checkpoint from train.
- The runtime environment (`env.modules`, `env.venv_activate`, `env.conda_activate`) must
  make `sforge-run-plan-executor`, `sforge-artifact-sync`, `sforge-write-train-outputs`,
  and `sforge-write-attempt-result` available on compute nodes.
- Retries export `AI_INFRA_RESUME_FROM_CHECKPOINT`; structured modes also pass
  `--resume_from_checkpoint` to your training script.
- Train and eval run in the same Slurm job. Use `output.dependencies` only for
  batch-level sequencing between separate batches.
